verses.text: Then Joseph could not refrain himself before all them that stood by him; and he cried , Cause every man to go out from me. And there stood no man with him, while Joseph made himself known unto his brethren.
And he wept aloud : and the Egyptians and the house of Pharaoh heard.\f + \fr 45.2 \ft wept…: Heb. gave forth his voice in weeping\f*

And Joseph said unto his brethren , I \add am\add* Joseph ; doth my father yet live ? And his brethren could not answer him; for they were troubled at his presence.\f + \fr 45.3 \ft troubled: or, terrified\f*
And Joseph said unto his brethren , Come near to me, I pray you. And they came near. And he said , I \add am\add* Joseph your brother , whom ye sold into Egypt.

Now therefore be not grieved , nor angry with yourselves , that ye sold me hither: for God did send me before you to preserve life.\f + \fr 45.5 \ft nor…: Heb. neither let there be anger in your eyes\f*
For these two years \add hath\add* the famine \add been\add* in the land : and yet \add there are\add* five years , in the which \add there shall\add* neither \add be\add* earing nor harvest.
And God sent me before you to preserve you a posterity in the earth , and to save your lives by a great deliverance.\f + \fr 45.7 \ft to preserve…: Heb. to put for you a remnant\f*
So now \add it was\add* not you \add that\add* sent me hither, but God : and he hath made me a father to Pharaoh , and lord of all his house , and a ruler throughout all the land of Egypt.
Haste ye, and go up to my father , and say unto him, Thus saith thy son Joseph , God hath made me lord of all Egypt : come down unto me, tarry not:
And thou shalt dwell in the land of Goshen , and thou shalt be near unto me, thou, and thy children , and thy children’s children , and thy flocks , and thy herds , and all that thou hast:
And there will I nourish thee; for yet \add there are\add* five years of famine ; lest thou, and thy household , and all that thou hast, come to poverty.
And, behold, your eyes see , and the eyes of my brother Benjamin , that \add it is\add* my mouth that speaketh unto you.
And ye shall tell my father of all my glory in Egypt , and of all that ye have seen ; and ye shall haste and bring down my father hither.
And he fell upon his brother Benjamin’s neck , and wept ; and Benjamin wept upon his neck.
Moreover he kissed all his brethren , and wept upon them: and after that his brethren talked with him. \p

¶ And the fame thereof was heard in Pharaoh’s house , saying , Joseph’s brethren are come : and it pleased Pharaoh well , and his servants.\f + \fr 45.16 \ft pleased…: Heb. was good in the eyes of Pharaoh\f*
And Pharaoh said unto Joseph , Say unto thy brethren , This do ye; lade your beasts , and go , get you unto the land of Canaan ;
And take your father and your households , and come unto me: and I will give you the good of the land of Egypt , and ye shall eat the fat of the land.
Now thou art commanded , this do ye; take you wagons out of the land of Egypt for your little ones , and for your wives , and bring your father , and come.
Also regard not your stuff ; for the good of all the land of Egypt \add is\add* yours.\f + \fr 45.20 \ft regard…: Heb. let not your eye spare, etc.\f*
And the children of Israel did so: and Joseph gave them wagons , according to the commandment of Pharaoh , and gave them provision for the way.\f + \fr 45.21 \ft commandment: Heb. mouth\f*
To all of them he gave each man changes of raiment ; but to Benjamin he gave three hundred \add pieces\add* of silver , and five changes of raiment.

And to his father he sent after this \add manner;\add* ten asses laden with the good things of Egypt , and ten she asses laden with corn and bread and meat for his father by the way.\f + \fr 45.23 \ft laden…: Heb. carrying\f*
So he sent his brethren away , and they departed : and he said unto them, See that ye fall not out by the way. \p
¶ And they went up out of Egypt , and came into the land of Canaan unto Jacob their father ,

And told him, saying , Joseph \add is\add* yet alive , and he \add is\add* governor over all the land of Egypt. And Jacob’s heart fainted , for he believed them not.\f + \fr 45.26 \ft Jacob’s: Heb. his\f*
And they told him all the words of Joseph , which he had said unto them: and when he saw the wagons which Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of Jacob their father revived :
And Israel said , \add It is\add* enough ; Joseph my son \add is\add* yet alive : I will go and see him before I die.
